::DarkMouse::

*She felt the blasts hit and she fell back.  She landed on a small patch of 
unscorched grass.  She looked up and saw the sky, heavy with smoke.  She 
just lay there, her gun in her hand.  She felt no pain.  No pain.  She 
wanted to just pass on to the other side.  She felt it call her.  THe soft 
voice of the Matrix called to her.  But she felt something inside say that 
now was not her time.  Not now it was not her time.  She closed her optics 
and saught strength in herself to move.  She opened her optics and slowly, 
very slowly rose to her knees.  Then she rose to her feet.  She aimed her 
gun at Bumblebee and fired.*

"Today, I shall be a Maximal."

*She kept on firing.  She knew not where this renewed strength came from, 
but she was glad to have it.*
